    <p class="text-gray-300">The S key schedules take a key and from it generate a sequence of <em>T</em> key words <em>k</em>0, . . . , <em>kT</em>−1, where <em>T</em> is the number of rounds. The effect of the single round function <em>R<sup>k</sup><sup>i</sup></em> is shown in Figure <a href="#page-17-0">4.1.</a> Encryption is then the composition <em>R<sup>k</sup>T</em>−<sup>1</sup> ◦ · · · ◦ <em>R<sup>k</sup></em><sup>1</sup> ◦ <em>R<sup>k</sup></em><sup>0</sup> , read from right to left.</p>

